# Database of awards and grants for HiiiWAV (2025-11-30 19:01Z)

_**User (2025-11-30 19:01Z)**_

Create a database of previous awards and grants that have been won by HiiiWAV, and then our the artists that are our participants and our team like our staff. 



Starting with HiiiWAV, and then I want to be able to filter and find, create lists of all the awards of the various, like, oh, Alphabet Rockers won these awards. They're a participant. Or ElectroSpit, they won these awards, and there's a list. Or the HiiiWAV Proper, the organization has won and have a list of all the awards.



So we want some common fields for each award, like the date it was awarded, the name of the award, the awarding entity. You could add some money if there was part or what the prize was. And like a description of the award and maybe some notable facts about it, like additional information and links to the awarding organization and link to the award page if there is one.



Suggest anything else that would be important, and the purpose of this is so that we can later create pages on our website that are complete that talk about all the awards that different entities that were related to HiiiWAV have won including HiiiWAV.

Done. The awards database schema is now live in your database with three new tables:

**`entities`** - For HiiiWAV, participant artists, and staff:
- Full profile support (bio, shortBio, image, website)
- Social links as JSONB (instagram, twitter, spotify, youtube, etc.)
- Type field (`organization`, `participant`, `staff`)
- Genre for artists, role for staff

**`awards`** - For tracking all awards/grants:
- Award details (name, awardingEntity, description, notableFacts)
- Date tracking (awardDate or year fallback)
- Prize info (prizeAmount in cents, prizeDescription)
- Status tracking (`won`, `nominated`, `finalist`, `honorable_mention`)
- Category (`grant`, `award`, `fellowship`, `recognition`, `nomination`)
- URLs (awardingOrgUrl, awardPageUrl, pressUrl)

**`award_recipients`** - Junction table for many-to-many:
- Links awards to entities
- Optional recipientRole (`primary`, `collaborator`, `featured`)
- Cascade delete on both FKs

+ import { NextResponse } from 'next/server'
+ import { db } from '@/db'
+ import { awards, awardRecipients, entities } from '@/db/schema'
+ import { desc, eq } from 'drizzle-orm'
+ 
+ export async function GET(req: Request) {
+   try {
+     const { searchParams } = new URL(req.url)
+     const entityId = searchParams.get('entityId')
+     
+     if (entityId) {
+       // Get awards for a specific entity
+       const entityAwards = await db
+         .select({
+           award: awards,
+           recipientRole: awardRecipients.recipientRole,
+         })
+         .from(awards)
+         .innerJoin(awardRecipients, eq(awards.id, awardRecipients.awardId))
+         .where(eq(awardRecipients.entityId, parseInt(entityId)))
+         .orderBy(desc(awards.year), desc(awards.awardDate))
+       
+       return NextResponse.json(entityAwards.map(r =&gt; ({ ...r.award, recipientRole: r.recipientRole })))
+     }
+     
+     // Get all awards with their recipients
+     const allAwards = await db.select().from(awards).orderBy(desc(awards.year), desc(awards.awardDate))
+     
+     // Get recipients for each award
+     const awardsWithRecipients = await Promise.all(
+       allAwards.map(async (award) =&gt; {
+         const recipients = await db
+           .select({
+             entity: entities,
+             recipientRole: awardRecipients.recipientRole,
+           })
+           .from(awardRecipients)
+           .innerJoin(entities, eq(awardRecipients.entityId, entities.id))
+           .where(eq(awardRecipients.awardId, award.id))
+         
+         return {
+           ...award,
+           recipients: recipients.map(r =&gt; ({ ...r.entity, recipientRole: r.recipientRole })),
+         }
+       })
+     )
+     
+     return NextResponse.json(awardsWithRecipients)
+   } catch (error) {
+     console.error('Error fetching awards:', error)
+     return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Failed to fetch awards' }, { status: 500 })
+   }
+ }
+ 
+ export async function POST(req: Request) {
+   try {
+     const body = await req.json()
+     
+     // Create the award
+     const [award] = await db.insert(awards).values({
+       slug: body.slug,
+       name: body.name,
+       awardingEntity: body.awardingEntity || 'Unknown',
+       awardDate: body.awardDate || null,
+       year: body.year || null,
+       category: body.category || null,
+       status: body.status || 'won',
+       prizeAmount: body.prizeAmount || null,
+       prizeDescription: body.prizeDescription || null,

+       const recipientValues = body.recipientIds.map((entityId: number, index: number) =&gt; ({
+         awardId: award.id,
+         entityId,
+         recipientRole: index === 0 ? 'primary' : 'collaborator',

+       
+       await db.insert(awardRecipients).values(recipientValues)
